In a large saute pan on MEDIUM high heat, cook the curry paste and the paprika in the oil for 30 seconds being careful not to burn it. Add the coconut milk, fish sauce, sugar, lime, and basil. Add the Broccoli Stir-Fry and cook for 4 minutes, allowing the vegetables to heat up thoroughly. Add the sliced beef and continue to cook for 2 minutes until beef is cooked through. Serve on top of steamed Jasmine Rice